HEADWORD: Antiparallels
<hw>An`ti*par"al*lels</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Straight lines or planes which make angles in
some respect opposite in character to those made by parallel lines or
planes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiparalytic</ent>⟦br⟧
